title: Janice Cayman
text:
Janice Cayman (born 12 October 1988) is a <a href="Belgium">Belgian</a> <a href="Women%27s%20association%20football">football</a> <a href="midfielder">attacking midfielder</a> currently playing for <a href="Olympique%20Lyonnais%20F%C3%A9minin">Olympique Lyonnais</a> in the <a href="Division%201%20F%C3%A9minine">D1 Féminine</a>.
Career.
She previously played for <a href="Montpellier%20HSC%20%28Ladies%29">Montpellier HSC</a> and <a href="FCF%20Juvisy">FCF Juvisy</a> in the <a href="Division%201%20F%C3%A9minine">French First Division</a>, <a href="Oud-Heverlee%20Leuven%20%28women%29">OH Leuven</a> and <a href="DVC%20Eva%27s%20Tienen">DVC Eva's Tienen</a> in the <a href="Belgian%20Women%27s%20First%20Division">Belgian First Division</a> and <a href="Florida%20State%20Seminoles%20women%27s%20soccer">Florida State Seminoles</a> in the <a href="NCAA">NCAA</a>, also playing the <a href="UEFA%20Women%27s%20Cup">European Cup</a> with Tienen.
She is a member of the <a href="Belgium%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Belgian national team</a> and scored four goals during their appearance at the <a href="2016%20Algarve%20Cup">2016 Algarve Cup</a>, making her top scorer of that tournament. On 12 November 2019, Cayman played her 100th match for Belgium against <a href="Lithuania%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Lithuania</a>.
